Section 6   	   MASSAGE OILS - USES & BENEFITS

			by Jan Blacktopp, R.M.T.
			blacktopp@interhop.net

	Read about Jan Blacktopp on our Meet the Team
	page; http://www.Life-Choices.com/team.html
----------

	  It seems that everything good for you these days has 
its roots in antiquity. Centuries ago, all these same types 
of medicine and healing techniques were practised in everyday 
use.

        The Roman Empire, which spanned 5000 years, was one of 
those cultures where massage, essential oils, luxurious baths 
and herbal formulas were used extensively to enhance health and 
beauty.

        Massage indicates the rubbing, kneading, pushing or 
sweeping of skin, muscles & joints of the body. Anyone can perform 
massage. A newborn usually receives his first massage upon his 
arrival here as mom & dads caress the face & head of their bundle 
of joy.

        When a toddler is ill or cranky, a mother will caress & 
soothe the child by gentle touch. When mothers rub our chest with 
linament when we had a cold, her hands somehow had some magic 
attached as you always felt better from that little rub. Essential 
oils were already added to those chest linaments. Now we have the 
access to make our own mixtures.

        Massage & essential oils may be the remedy you need to help 
you recuperate from a stressful work week, injury or illness. 
Studies have shown that regular massage once a month increases the 
efficiency of the immune system, increases mobility and decreases 
stress and muscle tension. Massage oils can be made at home, 
purchased at stores or obtained from your Aromatherapist or Massage 
Therapist.

You can make some at-home remedies yourself:

For the common cold, massage this blend around the chest, neck, 
& sinus areas:

Lemon		1 drop       
Eucalyptus    2 drops    
Rosemary	3 drops
Blend this into 1 tsp of vegetable or almond oil


Influenza
If you are shivery & cold, and feel that you have the onset of 
something more, take a warm bath to which the following oils 
have been added:

Tea tree	2 drops    
Lavender	2 drops     
Thyme		2 drops
Then:  massage your whole body with the following:
Tea tree	2 drops    
Eucalyptus	3 drops
Blend this into 1 tsp of vegetable/almond oil and go to bed.  

These essential oils have been shown to increase the immune 
system and can be used in the prevention of flu & colds when 
exposed to them.

Back Pain Formula
Massage this into any backache to ease pain:
Peppermint	10 drops   
